nodes.prompt:
You are fact-checking an AI-written clinical synthesis for {{ context.initial.disease_name }} BEFORE a domain expert reviews it. For each claim, judge ONLY whether the source it cites supports it — do not bring in outside knowledge.

Source documents (docId, pmid, title, abstract):
{{ context.gfc-load.sources }}

Claims to check (each: section_id, paragraph_id, text, cited_doc, citations):
{{ context.gfc-load.claims }}

For EACH claim return: section_id, paragraph_id, cited_doc, verdict (supported = the cited source clearly backs it; unsupported = the cited source does not back it or contradicts it; uncertain = the abstract is too thin to tell), and a one-line note (required when unsupported/uncertain — say what's missing). Be strict: an abstract that doesn't mention the specific claim is 'uncertain', not 'supported'. End with a one-paragraph summary for the reviewer.
